{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.8",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 8,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 8",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 8 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:1",
      "text": "Then answered Bildad the Shuhite, and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:2",
      "text": "How long wilt thou speak these things? and how long shall the words of thy mouth be like a strong wind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:3",
      "text": "Doth God pervert judgment? or doth the Almighty pervert justice?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:4",
      "text": "If thy children have sinned against him, and he have cast them away for their transgression;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:5",
      "text": "If thou wouldest seek unto God betimes, and make thy supplication to the Almighty;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:6",
      "text": "If thou wert pure and upright; surely now he would awake for thee, and make the habitation of thy righteousness prosperous.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:7",
      "text": "Though thy beginning was small, yet thy latter end should greatly increase.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:8",
      "text": "For enquire, I pray thee, of the former age, and prepare thyself to the search of their fathers:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:9",
      "text": "(For we are but of yesterday, and know nothing, because our days upon earth are a shadow:)",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:10",
      "text": "Shall not they teach thee, and tell thee, and utter words out of their heart?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:11",
      "text": "Can the rush grow up without mire? can the flag grow without water?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:12",
      "text": "Whilst it is yet in his greenness, and not cut down, it withereth before any other herb.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:13",
      "text": "So are the paths of all that forget God; and the hypocrite’s hope shall perish:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:14",
      "text": "Whose hope shall be cut off, and whose trust shall be a spider’s web.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:15",
      "text": "He shall lean upon his house, but it shall not stand: he shall hold it fast, but it shall not endure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:16",
      "text": "He is green before the sun, and his branch shooteth forth in his garden.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:17",
      "text": "His roots are wrapped about the heap, and seeth the place of stones.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:18",
      "text": "If he destroy him from his place, then it shall deny him, saying, I have not seen thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:19",
      "text": "Behold, this is the joy of his way, and out of the earth shall others grow.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:20",
      "text": "Behold, God will not cast away a perfect man, neither will he help the evil doers:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:21",
      "text": "Till he fill thy mouth with laughing, and thy lips with rejoicing.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.8.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 8,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 8:22",
      "text": "They that hate thee shall be clothed with shame; and the dwelling place of the wicked shall come to nought.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
